1
00:00:02,999 --> 00:00:05,201
It's mind-boggling
to think that ending a human

2
00:00:05,201 --> 00:00:08,004
life could be
considered a matter of personal choice,

3
00:00:08,004 --> 00:00:10,740
like choosing a career or dieting.

4
00:00:10,740 --> 00:00:12,842
Let's put some of
the pro-abortion arguments in

5
00:00:12,842 --> 00:00:16,145
perspective by
applying the two-year-old test.

6
00:00:16,145 --> 00:00:19,882
Whenever there's a reference
to a fetus, substitute two-year-old.

7
00:00:19,882 --> 00:00:23,653
For example, it's the right
of every two-year-old to be wanted.

8
00:00:23,653 --> 00:00:27,190
We're not pro-killing
two-year-olds, we're pro-choice.

9
00:00:27,190 --> 00:00:29,892
Unless you're prepared
to adopt this two-year-old, you

10
00:00:29,892 --> 00:00:33,029
have no right to tell the
mother she should not kill her.

11
00:00:33,029 --> 00:00:36,566
If we don't make it possible for
the mother to kill her two-year-old safely,

12
00:00:36,566 --> 00:00:40,403
then she'll do it unsafely and
possibly put her own health in danger.

13
00:00:40,403 --> 00:00:43,306
That sounds shocking,
but you can see the logic.

14
00:00:43,306 --> 00:00:46,142
Why should killing a
pre-born baby be any less

15
00:00:46,142 --> 00:00:50,279
monstrous than killing a
toddler, a teenager, or an adult?

16
00:00:50,279 --> 00:00:53,916
They're all human beings at
different stages of development.

